name: Jacques Lacan
abstract: Jacques Marie Émile Lacan was a French psychoanalyst and psychiatrist who made prominent contributions to psychoanalysis and philosophy, and has been called "the most controversial psycho-analyst since Freud".
related_books: The Four Fundamental Concepts of Psychoanalysis (1973)
Ecrits: The First Complete Edition in English
